The Nigeria Institute of Building (NIOB) formed in 1967 and saddled with the responsibility of promoting professionalism in the industry has decried poor practices which is responsible for building collapse in the country. The forum held a national rally yesterday in Kaduna to sensitise the populace on the ills bedeviling the sector. The Kaduna State chapter of the NIOB in solidarity with the national body held a procession from Kaduna polytechnic, Barnawa to the Sir Kashim Ibrahim house where the Kaduna State chairman, Abdulrasheed Sirajo said, the menace of building collapse occasioned by poor practices still stares the nation in the face. According to him, there was the need to employ the services of professional builders. “There is need for the general public and government institutions to always engage a professional builder to avoid occurrences of building collapse in the country. The director of administration and finance in the ministry of housing and urban development, Muhammed Tajudeen, reeled out the state government’s effort in curtailing quacks in the industry. 